data.title: Nicole Kidman To Star In New Woody Allen Film
data.meta_description: Nicole Kidman will star in the new Woody Allen film, Variety reported on Thursday. The Aussie beauty joins the already announced Naomi Watts, Antonio Banderas,...
data.text:
Nicole Kidman will star in the new Woody Allen film, Variety reported on Thursday.

The Aussie beauty joins the already announced Naomi Watts, Antonio Banderas, Josh Brolin, Anthony Hopkins and "Slumdog Millionaire" star Freida Pinto in the as-of-yet untitled film.

VIEW THE PHOTOS: Nicole Kidman- From The Outback To The Oscars!

Kidman last starred in "Australia," alongside Hugh Jackman.

She has several projects currently in development, including the drama "The Danish Girl" opposite Charlize Theron; the con caper "Monte Carlo" and the epic period film "Alexander The Great," co-starring Leonardo DiCaprio.

VIEW THE PHOTOS: 'Slumdog' Beauty Freida Pinto

Woody Allen's latest film, "Whatever Works," will be released June 19, starring Henry Cavill and Evan Rachel Wood.
